-Node.js is a js runtime built on chrome v8 javascript engine.
-It is javascript running on a server
-Node.js runs the v8 js engine, the core of Google Chrome, outside of the browser. This allows Node.js to be very performant
- Node.js runs on various platforms(Windows, Linux, Unix, MacOS X, etc.)


-In 2009 Ryan Dahl created node js.

-When to use Node JS:
>I/O Bound
>Data streaming applications
>Real time chat systems